HEADWORD: Album Græcum
<hw>Al"bum Gr⟦ae⟧"cum</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[L., Greek
white.]</ety> <def>Dung of dogs or hyenas, which becomes white by
exposure to air. It is used in dressing leather, and was formerly used
in medicine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Albumin</ent>⟦br⟧
